+0.076}_{-0.077}-0.171^{+0.214}_{-0.196}z$. Although not the more likely\nmodel, this evolved $\\gamma$ case also fits the data well, with a negative and\nmild evolution for both low and high redshift samples.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 30 Mar 2023 14:23:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-08"}
